    "Imputation and adjustment\n",
    "===============\n",
    "\n",
    "Theory underlying the adjustment of sample sizes in GWAS (molQTL) summary statistics\n",
    "------------------\n",
    "\n",
    "For a given gene (or protein), we defined $b_j^{(c)}$ as the molQTL effect for SNP $j$ with the current sample size and $b_j^{(t)}$ as that with the target sample size. Under the assumption of normality and unit phenotypic variance, the joint distribution of $b_j^{(c)}$ and $b_j^{(t)}$ can be approximated by a bivariate normal distribution.\n",
    "\n",
    "For each gene, given the marginal effect-size vector $\\mathbf{b}^{(c)}$ and LD matrix $\\mathbf{R}$, the conditional distribution of $\\mathbf{b}^{(t)} \\mid \\mathbf{b}^{(c)}$ is:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\\mathbf{b}^{(t)} \\mid \\mathbf{b}^{(c)} \\sim \\mathcal{N}\\left(\\mathbf{b}^{(c)}, \\left(\\frac{1}{n_t} - \\frac{1}{n_c} \\right)\\mathbf{R} \\right)$$\n",
    "\n",
    "where $n_c$ and $n_t$ are the current and target sample sizes for each molQTL within that gene, respectively, with $\\mathbf{b}^{(c)}$ used as a surrogate of the true effect sizes.\n",
    "\n",
    "Eigen-decomposition with a maximum cut-off of variance explained ($\\rho = 0.995$) was applied to the LD matrix to generate a pseudo-inverse of $\\mathbf{R}$. The summary statistics under the target sample size were then estimated as:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\\mathbf{b}^{(t)} \\mid \\mathbf{b}^{(c)} = \\mathbf{b}^{(c)} + \\sqrt{\\frac{1}{n_t} - \\frac{1}{n_c}} \\, \\mathbf{U} \\mathbf{\\Lambda}^{1/2} \\boldsymbol{\\xi}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "where $\\mathbf{U}$ and $\\mathbf{\\Lambda}$ are matrices of eigenvectors and eigenvalues of the LD matrix $\\mathbf{R}$, and $\\xi_j \\sim \\mathcal{N}(0, 1)$ is a standard normal random variable for SNP $j$.\n",
    "\n",
    "The marginal standard errors (SE) for $b^{(t)}$ and $b^{(c)}$ are:\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\\mathrm{SE}^{(t)} = \\sqrt{\\frac{1 - \\left(b^{(t)}\\right)^2}{n_t}}, \\quad \\mathrm{SE}^{(c)} = \\sqrt{\\frac{1 - \\left(b^{(c)}\\right)^2}{n_c}}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Equivalently, $\\mathrm{SE}^{(t)}$ can be estimated as:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\\mathrm{SE}^{(t)} = \\sqrt{\\frac{n_c}{n_t}} \\, \\mathrm{SE}^{(c)}$$"
   ]
  },

    "#############################################################\n",
    "### R demo for adjusting sample sizes in GWAS (molQTL) summary\n",
    "#############################################################\n",
    "rm(list = ls())\n",
    "suppressPackageStartupMessages({\n",
    "  library(tidyverse)\n",
    "  library(data.table)\n",
    "  library(patchwork)\n",
    "  library(latex2exp)\n",
    "  library(cowplot)\n",
    "})\n",
    "set.seed(1234)\n",
    "if (!requireNamespace(\"SBayesOmics\", quietly = TRUE)) {\n",
    "  devtools::install_github(\"ShouyeLiu/SBayesOmics\")\n",
    "}\n",
    "library(SBayesOmics)\n",
    "sumPath =  system.file(\"extdata/summary/\", package = \"SBayesOmics\")\n",
    "\n",
    "smrIndFileSuffix = \"ukbg-chr22-causal-model-50k-ind\"\n",
    "geneLDFile = paste0(sumPath,smrIndFileSuffix)\n",
    "geneSummaryFile = paste0(sumPath,smrIndFileSuffix)\n",
    "qtlP50K = downsampleN(geneSummaryFile,geneLDFile,targetN = 50000)\n",
    "qtlP10K = downsampleN(geneSummaryFile,geneLDFile,targetN = 10000)\n",
    "qtlP1K  = downsampleN(geneSummaryFile,geneLDFile,targetN = 1000)\n",
    "datPse<- rbind(qtlP50K,qtlP10K,qtlP1K)\n",
    "############################################################\n",
    "## specific theme\n",
    "themeLocal =  theme_bw() + theme(axis.text=element_text(size=10,face = \"bold\"),\n",
    " axis.title=element_text(size=10,face=\"bold\"),\n",
    " axis.title.x = element_text(size = 8.5),  # Adjust the size as needed\n",
    " axis.title.y = element_text(size = 8.5),\n",
    " legend.title=element_text(size=10,face=\"bold\"),\n",
    " legend.text=element_text(size=10,face = \"bold\"),\n",
    " panel.grid.major = element_line(color = \"white\", linewidth = 0.2),\n",
    " panel.grid.minor = element_line(color = \"white\", linewidth = 0.1),\n",
    " plot.subtitle = element_text(size = 9, face = \"bold\", hjust = 0.5),\n",
    " strip.text = element_text(size = 5.5),\n",
    " aspect.ratio = 1  ,\n",
    " axis.text.x = element_text(size = 8,angle = 45,hjust = 1),\n",
    " axis.text.y = element_text(size = 8),\n",
    " legend.position.inside = c(0.65, 0.12),\n",
    " legend.background = element_rect(fill = alpha(\"white\", 0.5) )\n",
    " )\n",
    "datPse$N = factor(datPse$N)\n",
    "mycolors = c(\"#45b787\", \"#f03f24\",\"black\")\n",
    "##########################################\n",
    "pMBeta = datPse %>%  as.data.table() %>%\n",
    " ggplot(aes(x = betaR,y = betaPse,color = N,shape  = N)) +\n",
    " geom_abline(intercept = 0, slope = 1,linetype = \"dashed\", color = \"grey\") +\n",
    " geom_point(size = 0.9, stroke = 1)  +\n",
    " xlab(\"True eQTL effect\") +\n",
    " ylab(\"Estimated eQTL effect\") +\n",
    " scale_fill_manual(values=mycolors) +\n",
    " scale_color_manual(values=mycolors)+\n",
    " facet_wrap(~ GeneID,scales = \"free\") +\n",
    " themeLocal + # + theme(legend.position = \"none\") +\n",
    " labs(color  = \"Sample size\", shape = \"Sample size\") +\n",
    " labs(tag = 'a')\n",
    "pMSe = datPse %>%  as.data.table() %>%\n",
    " ggplot(aes(x = seR,y = sePse,color = N,shape = N )) +\n",
    " geom_abline(intercept = 0, slope = 1,linetype = \"dashed\", color = \"grey\") +\n",
    " geom_point( size = 0.9,stroke = 1)  +\n",
    " xlab(\"True eQTL standard error (SE)\") +\n",
    " ylab(\"Estimated eQTL standard error (SE)\") +\n",
    " scale_fill_manual(values=mycolors) +\n",
    " scale_color_manual(values=mycolors)+\n",
    " facet_wrap(~ GeneID,scales = \"free\") +\n",
    " themeLocal +\n",
    " labs(color  = \"Sample size\", shape = \"Sample size\") +\n",
    " # guides(color = guide_legend(title = \"Sample size\")) +\n",
    " labs(tag = 'b')\n",
    "fplot <- plot_grid(pMBeta, pMSe, ncol = 2, rel_widths = c(1, 1))\n",
    "# # Show it\n",
    "options(repr.plot.width = 10, repr.plot.height = 5)  # adjust size\n",
    "print(fplot)\n"
   ]
